    "plan_content": "The plan is ready. Here's a summary of what will be implemented to add `Bun.INI`:\n\n## Summary\n\n### Files to **create** (3):\n1. **`src/interchange/ini.zig`** — Pure Zig INI parser. Iterates lines, handles sections (`[name]` → nested objects), `key = value` pairs (all values as strings), comment lines (`;`/`#`), and inline comment stripping. Returns `Expr` AST using the same `std.array_list.Managed(G.Property)` + `.moveFromList` pattern as the JSON5 parser.\n\n2. **`src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`** — JS API binding following JSON5Object.zig exactly. Exposes `parse` (accepts string/buffer, returns JS object via `exprToJS`) and `stringify` (iterates root JS object, emits flat `key = value` lines and `[section]` blocks using `wtf.StringBuilder`).\n\n3. **`test/js/bun/ini/ini.test.ts`** — Full test suite covering parse (sections, comments, inline comments, empty input, errors) and stringify (flat objects, section objects, edge cases).\n\n### Files to **modify** (6):\n4. **`src/interchange.zig`** — Add `pub const ini` import\n5. **`src/bun.js/api.zig`** — Add `pub const INIObject` import\n6. **`src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig`** — 4 additions: lazy property declaration, `exportAll()` registration, `getINIObject()` getter, and bottom import\n7. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h`** — Add `macro(INI)` to `FOR_EACH_GETTER`\n8. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp`** — Add `INI BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to the bunObjectTable\n9. **`packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`** — Add `namespace INI` with full JSDoc",
